Input: The industry that makes plastic army figures uses a small fraction of the plastic demanded for all purposes.  On this basis,  we can conclude that the army-figures industry is most likely a(n) Choices: a) increasing-cost industry b) constant-cost industry c) decreasing-cost industry d) profit-making industry 
 Output:
 First,  we need to understand the concept of cost industries.  An increasing-cost industry is one where the production costs rise as more firms enter the market.  A constant-cost industry is one where production costs remain the same regardless of the number of firms.  A decreasing-cost industry is one where production costs fall as more firms enter theThe correct answer is {'sol': 'c'}
